{"metadata":{"title":"enumerated()","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"Swift","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:STsE10enumerateds18EnumeratedSequenceVyxGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:SS8UTF8ViewV"},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UTF8View/enumerated()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Returns a sequence of pairs (","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"), where ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" represents a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" represents an element of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the sequence."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UTF8View"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/string/utf8view/enumerated()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A sequence of pairs enumerating the sequence."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example enumerates the characters of the string “Swift” and prints"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each character along with its place in the string."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["for (n, c) in \"Swift\".enumerated() {","    print(\"\\(n): '\\(c)'\")","}","// Prints \"0: 'S'\"","// Prints \"1: 'w'\"","// Prints \"2: 'i'\"","// Prints \"3: 'f'\"","// Prints \"4: 't'\""]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you enumerate a collection, the integer part of each pair is a counter","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the enumeration, but is not necessarily the index of the paired value.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"These counters can be used as indices only in instances of zero-based,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"integer-indexed collections, such as ","type":"text"},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"ContiguousArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"other collections the counters may be out of range or of the wrong type","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to use as an index. To iterate over the elements of a collection with its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"indices, use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"zip(_:_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This example iterates over the indices and elements of a set, building a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"list consisting of indices of names with five or fewer letters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let names: Set = [\"Sofia\", \"Camilla\", \"Martina\", \"Mateo\", \"Nicolás\"]","var shorterIndices: [Set<String>.Index] = []","for (i, name) in zip(names.indices, names) {","    if name.count <= 5 {","        shorterIndices.append(i)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that the "},{"code":"shorterIndices","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" array holds the indices of the shorter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"names in the "},{"code":"names","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" set, you can use those indices to access elements in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the set."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["for i in shorterIndices {","    print(names[i])","}","// Prints \"Sofia\"","// Prints \"Mateo\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"O(1)","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Complexity"}]}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UTF8View/enumerated()":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns a sequence of pairs (","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":"), where ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"n","type":"text"}]},{"text":" represents a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"x","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" represents an element of","type":"text"},{